title: For Sale:  TIKKA T3 HUNTER IN .308 WIN WITH NIKON SCOPE, TALLEY ONE-PIECE RINGS
postcontent:
For sale is this Tikka T3 Hunter in .308 Winchester.

I bought it roughly 10 months ago planning to get into longer distance shooting and hunting eventually, but my situation has changed and I no longer have the time for that side of the hobby.

It's a beautifully well put together rifle. Free floated barrel, ridiculously smooth bolt operation, crisp adjustable trigger, I'd buy it again in a heartbeat, I just don't need it.

It's magazine fed, 3+1 capacity, safety w a 2 dot system on the bolt and safety position letting you know its status. Ejects and feeds smoothly. I took it shooting once and put ~5-10 rounds through it, I can't remember exactly.

The barrel is 22 7/16" long, cold hammer forged with an 11" rate of twist. The trigger is adjustable between 2 and 4 pounds. The magazine is removable with the catch located just forward of the magazine when inserted. It is plastic and holds 3 rounds.

The scope is a Nikon Prostaff 4-12x40mm with the BDC reticle. It is mounted on Talley One-piece (Low) rings/bases. These are very solid mounts and in my opinion give the rifle a lot cleaner look than regular rings/mounts. Both the scope and rings were purchased for this rifle so they're both new too.

I'm asking $950, but feel free to make an offer.
Not that big on trades but it depends on what you have.

Thanks for looking!
